      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783641842563,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Synchronous Communication\nHow it works: One service calls another directly\nand waits/blocks for the response before\nproceeding.\nExample: Standard HTTP requests.\n2. Asynchronous Communication\nHow it works: One service pushes a task to a\nbroker (like a queue or pub/sub) and\nimmediately moves on without waiting for the\ntask to be completed. Another service pulls and\nprocesses it in its own time.\nExample: Message Queues (Redis, RabbitMQ)\nand Pub/Sub systems.\n3. WebSockets (The Debatable Middle Ground)\nWhy it's debatable: You send data over the wire\nimmediately (synchronous feel), but you do not\nwait for a response/acknowledgement\n(asynchronous feel).",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Synchronous Communication\nHow it works: One service calls another directly and waits/blocks for the response before proceeding.\nExample: Standard HTTP requests.\n2. Asynchronous Communication\nHow it works: One service pushes a task to a broker (like a queue or pub/sub) and immediately moves on without waiting for the task to be completed. Another service pulls and processes it in its own time.\nExample: Message Queues (Redis, RabbitMQ) and Pub/Sub systems.\n3. WebSockets (The Debatable Middle Ground)\nWhy it's debatable: You send data over the wire immediately (synchronous feel), but you do not wait for a response/acknowledgement (asynchronous feel).",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
